I"<p>Yarimar Bonilla is Associate Professor of anthropology and Latino &amp; Caribbean Studies at Rutgers University, where she is on the executive board for the Advanced Institute for Critical Caribbean Studies. She teaches and writes about social movements, colonial legacies, and the politics of history in the Atlantic World. She is the author of <em>Non-Sovereign Futures: French Caribbean Politics in the Wake of Disenchantment</em> (2015) and is currently working on a book project about the statehood movement in Puerto Rico.</p>
